Game: Brothers - A Tale of Two Sons

Notes:
Civ V
Bomb an enemy city with a B-17.
Space Victory using the Order Ideology
Civ V Save: When starting war within the great wall, all your units are forced out. Try an autosave to find a save where most of your units are in friendly territory, so you can upgrade then.

To Play 
3+ players 
A battle royale of head to head

Goal:
Make sets of 4 (eg: 4 6's).
The player with the most sets of 4 at the end wins
 
In order to play a set, you must first play a Queen or a King.
Queens allow 2 sets
Kings allow 3 sets
 
Players must top-up to 5 cards after playing
 
If a jack is drawn, the drawing player must lay down, along with the Jack, all of the cards in their hand. Top back up to 5 cards afterwards.
 
Unique sets worth 2 points:
6969
 
The ace set is worth 3 points.
 
Aces can also be used to steal Queens & Kings.
2 Aces to steal Queen. 3 Aces to steal King.
 
 
One Ace used in this way is added to the victims hand, extending past 5 cards if need be.
The other Ace(s) are deposited in any of the piles: Jacks, Discard, Draw
All sets resting on stolen Queens/Kings are split among all present Jacks
 
Drawing a joker increases your hand-size to 6.
Drawing the second joker shrinks your hand size back to 5, and banishes one of your sets from the game permanently.
 
Players can, on their turn:
 
1. Discard cards. 
    a. Alternate between the discard pile, and any Jack pile, always staring with the discard pile
    b. If there are no jacks, discard the desired number of cards into the discard pile
2. Play 1 King or Queen
3. Play a set
4. Play Ace(s)
5. Draw 1 card from each jack-pile
6. Draw from the discard pile.
7. Draw from the stock pile

Game: Talk it Out / Act it Out
THE GREAT OXFORD GAME OF THE ENGLISH LANGUAGE
